title: Interaction of high-energy protons and alpha particles with iodine-127

x4freetext: Interaction of high-energy protons and alpha particles
with iodine-127

Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory, Livermore, CA, United States of America

x4freetext: The targets were prepared from sheets of cellulose
acetate containing known amounts of iodine in the form
of iodoform. The iodine content of the films was rough
15 to 35 mg I/cm2.
The target consisted of a stack of foils in the
following order: 1-mil aluminum, the iodine-containing
film, 1-mil aluminum, 3-mil aluminum monitor of known
weight and 10mil aluminum.
The over-all experimental accuracy of the measurements
was approximately +-25% for the nuclides with known
decay schemes and for the incident energies at which
the monitor cross section had been measured.
Data taken from PR,119,1368,1960--tables I, II,
and III.
